 New Hires' RSU Conversion and Vesting Process Summary:

For new hires receiving restricted stock units (RSUs), the grant target value specified in their offer letter is converted to U.S. dollars using a 9-month average exchange rate that ends on the first business day of the Hooli fiscal quarter corresponding to their start date. This conversion isn't necessary if the offer letter is already in U.S. dollars. The total RSU allocation is then divided by the average closing stock price over 21 consecutive business days up until the end of the month they started work, rounding down to the nearest whole unit. For instance, with a €200,000 grant starting May 2, 2022, and an average stock price of $177.91, approximately 1,300 RSUs would be allocated. These grants become available on the eleventh business day after the start month, and the vested shares appear in the employee's Schwab account during the second full week post-grant. Employees can check their vesting schedules via the Schwab platform.

